{
  "texts": [
    "Later, feature extraction, a process in which pretrained DL models reduce the dimensionality of input images to smaller matrices or vectors, became the stateof-the-art method [25,[55][56][57][58][59] (Fig 1).",
    "Another change in model design was introduced after 2017, in which transformer neural networks [60,61] were developed.",
    "These models can weigh parts of their input differently based on an attention mechanism and parallelize the processing of multiple parts of the input data in a computationally efficient way.",
    "In 2022, Chen et al. [62] (Fig.",
    "2a) predicted survival through the use of vision transformers, which were able to outperform convolution-based models in many cancer types.In summary, during the last years, AI in pathology underwent many changes and trends."
  ]
}